annotationA: SECIS-binding protein 2; Selenocysteine insertion sequence binding; RNA stem-loop binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: selenocysteine incorporation
annotationB: Selenide, water dikinase is a selenophosphate synthetase (SPS) that catalyzes the synthesis of selenophosphate from selenide, ATP, and water, producing AMP and inorganic phosphate as products. SPS are well conserved proteins involved in selenium metabolism; Belongs to the selenophosphate synthase 1 family. Class II subfamily
